 Basic]] \u2013 see [[List of BASIC dialects]] -->\n* [[Blockly]]\n* [[BlooP and FlooP|BlooP]]\n* [[Boo (programming language)|Boo]]\n* [[Boomerang (programming language)|Boomerang]]\n* [[Bosque (programming language)|Bosque]]\n* [[Bourne shell]] (including [[Bash (Unix shell)|bash]] and [[Korn shell|ksh]])\n<!-- [[Brainfuck]] belongs on the esoteric page -->\n<!-- [[Qualcomm Brew|BREW]] from its wiki page, it uses c/c++, not a language -->\n}}\n\n== C ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* [[C (programming language)|C]]\n* [[C--]] (C minus minus)\n* [[C++]] (C plus plus) \u2013 ISO/IEC 14882\n* [[C*]]\n* [[C Sharp (programming language)|C#]] (C sharp) \u2013 ISO/IEC 23270\n* [[C/AL]]\n* [[Cach\u00e9 ObjectScript]]\n<!-- [[Cach\u00e9 Basic]] is on the BASIC dialects list -->\n<!-- add csh in parantheses here, to remove duplicates-->\n* [[C Shell | C Shell (csh)]]\n* [[Caml]]\n* [[Cayenne (programming language)|Cayenne]]\n<!-- [[CBASIC]] - see [[List of BASIC dialects]] page -->\n* [[CDuce]]\n* [[Cecil (programming language)|Cecil]]\n* [[Cesil]]\n* [[C\u00e9u (programming language)|C\u00e9u]]\n* [[Ceylon (programming language)|Ceylon]]\n* [[CFEngine]]\n* [[Cg (programming language)|Cg]]\n* [[Ch (computer programming)|Ch]]\n* [[Chapel (programming language)|Chapel]]\n* [[Charm (language)|Charm]]\n* [[CHILL]]\n* [[CHIP-8]]\n* [[chomski]]\n* [[ChucK]]\n<!-- [[CICS]] is a transaction framework with macro processor, not a language, languages used are PL/I, COBOL, Java  -->\n* [[Cilk]]\n* [[Citrine (programming language)|Citrine]]\n* [[AS/400 Control Language|CL]] (IBM)\n* [[Claire (programming language)|Claire]]\n* [[Clarion (programming language)|Clarion]]\n* [[Clean (programming language)|Clean]]\n* [[Clipper (programming language)|Clipper]]\n* [[CLIPS (programming language)|CLIPS]]\n* [[CLIST]]\n* [[Clojure]]\n<!-- CLOS is under Common Lisp -->\n* [[CLU (programming language)|CLU]]\n* [[CMS-2 (programming language)|CMS-2]]\n* [[COBOL]] \u2013 ISO/IEC 1989\n* [[CobolScrip